President Barack Obama has declared November as National Entrepreneurship Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the important role that entrepreneurs have played in the country's history and economy. He emphasizes the need to support and empower entrepreneurs, particularly through initiatives such as immigration reform, accessible healthcare, and government support for small businesses. The President also mentions the importance of data accessibility, tax cuts, and programs like the White House Startup America initiative in fostering entrepreneurship. He calls for increased transparency and accountability globally and announces the formation of the President's Committee on Global Entrepreneurship. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate entrepreneurship and support aspiring entrepreneurs in their pursuit of innovation and a brighter future.